    "Such associations among centromeres and among telomeres, first observed in salamander embryos 111, have been observed in other animals 110, [113] [114] [115] [116] [117], fungi 110, 118, 119, and plants 109, 110, [120] [121] [122].",
    "Outside of mammals, Rabl-like contacts have been observed in a wide diversity of taxa.",
    "Hoencamp et al.",
    "surveyed 24 plant and animal species using Hi-C and observed Rabl-like patterns in 14 (58.3%) of them.",
    "Out of seven vertebrates sampled, however, only Xenopus laevis fibroblasts showed a Rabl-like pattern."
